158
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:21,960
Xu Xiangdong and I are your fans.

159
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:23,960
The three of us have formed a fan club

160
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,680
to follow you here

161
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:26,800
from the Northeast China.

162
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,520
Are you kidding?

163
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:30,320
My fan club only has three?

164
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:30,960
No!

165
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:33,240
We three are the main force.

166
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:34,080
We are big fans.

167
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:35,600
The entire school are your fans.

168
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:36,320
We represent them.

169
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,800
That sounds better.

170
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:38,800
Director.

171
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:41,600
I'd like to ask a question.

172
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:43,240
It's about this drama.

173
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:45,680
What story does it tell?

174
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,880
Since you are my big fan,

175
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,800
I'll tell you secretly, you know.

176
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,960
But the plot must not be disclosed.

177
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:52,544
Definitely.

178
00:06:52,544 --> 00:06:53,120
Keep a secret?

179
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:53,680
Sure.

180
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,240
A secret.

181
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:54,800
Certainly.

182
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:55,720
The story tells

183
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:58,000
that after aliens invaded Earth,

184
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,320
when the X country is at a loss,

185
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,600
our valiant Northeastern people

186
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:04,720
defeated them with local cultural arts.

187
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,320
Shocked, right?

188
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:07,720
Yes.

189
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:08,680
Totally shocked.

190
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,080
I wrote the script myself.

191
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:11,520
You must unleash your imagination.

192
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,520
But this kind of script,

193
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,160
from the audience's perspective,

194
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:16,680
wouldn't it seem a bit far-fetched?

195
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,520
What do you know?

196
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,560
It's a mix of martial arts, comedy,
and skits.

197
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:20,720
A new style of film.

198
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:22,840
As a ninth-generation pioneer director,

199
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,960
I guess, only I dare
to make something like this.

200
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:28,440
Director, I think you're right.

201
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,840
By the way,

202
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:33,800
about the three corpses...

203
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:35,680
Can I see

204
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:37,080
their playback?

205
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:37,720
Corpses?

206
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,320
What's there to shoot with them?

207
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:41,280
Why do you want to see that? Ridiculous.

208
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,560
Then, if we don't shoot them,

209
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:44,960
why are they needed?

210
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:46,240
See, you don't get it.

211
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,120
Filming requires focal points.

212
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,800
The script says there are three corpses.

213
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,080
Even if I don't shoot them,

214
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:53,400
there have to be three in place.

215
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,160
Understood?

216
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,800
Otherwise, it feels like

217
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:57,120
something is missing.

218
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:58,560
Right, what is it called?

219
00:07:58,880 --> 00:07:59,520
The soul.

220
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,680
Right, the soul.

221
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,520
Then, did the three corpses

222
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,240
act well or not?

223
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:05,320
I mean, about the soul,

224
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:06,880
